# Structural contracts

When changing behavior in app surfaces, check whether a **registry** owns the invariant and run the matching structural guards before PR.

## Surfaces

| Surface | Registry docs | Command |
|---------|---------------|---------|
| Offline field | `farmer-artifact-sync-registry.md`, `field-role-permission-registry.md`, `field-state-transition-registry.md` | `cd apps/offline-product && npm run qa:structural` |
| Dashboard | `dashboard-rbac-registry.md` | `cd apps/dashboard-product && npm run qa:structural` |
| Backend | `backend-structural-contracts.md` | `cd tracebud-backend && npm run qa:structural` |
| Marketing | `marketing-structural-contracts.md` | `cd apps/marketing && npm run qa:structural` |

Monorepo fan-out: `npm run qa:structural:monorepo` from repo root.

## Offline guards (bundled in `qa:structural`)

- `sync-parity-guard.mjs` — pipeline ↔ registry wiring
- `registry-md-parity-guard.mjs` — markdown ↔ TypeScript registry
- `pending-sync-registry-guard.mjs` — SQLite action types ↔ queue handlers
- `ui-reload-guard.mjs` — screen reload after restore
- `cross-device-smoke-wiring-guard.mjs` — DEVICE_SMOKE §12 + Maestro wiring
- `role-permission-guard.mjs`, `state-transition-guard.mjs`, `feature-doc-guard.mjs`, `analytics-slice-guard.mjs`

## Principles

1. Prefer fixing **class problems** in registry/orchestrator/guards, not one-off patches.
2. Update product-os when behavior changes: feature doc, `daily-log.md`, registry row.
3. Field cloud audit events must stay aligned across offline `farmerArtifactRegistry.ts` and backend `backendAuditEventRegistry.ts`.

Pre-commit: `.husky/pre-commit` → `scripts/pre-commit-structural-guard.mjs` (per-app when staged).

Runbook: `product-os/04-quality/structural-contracts-runbook.md`
